write_file({"contents": "# Provider ID Stability & Deprecation Policy\n\nVokda assigns every TTS provider a **machine-readable provider ID** — a short, stable, lower-kebab identifier used across the API, SDKs, catalog data, and synthesis pipelines. These IDs are the canonical way to reference a provider in code, configuration, and API payloads.\n\nIf you are integrating against Vokda’s API or SDK, pinning logic to these IDs is the supported and expected path. Client code that branches on `provider` / `providerId` fields should use the values below and rely on the stability contract described in this document.\n\n## Canonical Provider IDs\n\nVokda’s catalog currently recognises **25** providers. Every provider ID is stable once listed; additions happen only when new providers are onboarded.\n\n| Provider ID       | Provider Name      | Type           |\n|-------------------|--------------------|----------------|\n| `aws-polly`       | AWS Polly          | cloud_provider |\n| `azure-speech`    | Azure Speech       | cloud_provider |\n| `bark`            | Bark               | open_model     |\n| `cartesia`        | Cartesia           | cloud_provider |\n| `chatterbox`      | Chatterbox         | open_model     |\n| `chatterbox-turbo`| Chatterbox Turbo   | open_model     |\n| `deepgram`        | Deepgram           | cloud_provider |\n| `dia`             | Dia                | open_model     |\n| `edge-tts`        | Edge TTS           | cloud_provider |\n| `elevenlabs`      | ElevenLabs         | cloud_provider |\n| `gemini-tts`      | Gemini TTS         | cloud_provider |\n| `gcp-tts`         | Google Cloud TTS   | cloud_provider |\n| `kittentts`       | KittenTTS          | open_model     |\n| `kokoro`          | Kokoro             | open_model     |\n| `lmnt`            | LMNT               | cloud_provider |\n| `marvis`          | Marvis             | open_model     |\n| `openai`          | OpenAI             | cloud_provider |\n| `orpheus`         | Orpheus TTS        | open_model     |\n| `outetts`         | OuteTTS            | open_model     |\n| `pocket-tts`      | Pocket TTS         | open_model     |\n| `qwen3-tts`       | Qwen3 TTS          | open_model     |\n| `soprano`         | Soprano            | open_model     |\n| `spark-tts`       | Spark TTS          | open_model     |\n| `vibevoice`       | VibeVoice          | open_model     |\n| `voxcpm`          | VoxCPM             | open_model     |\n\n## Stability Contract\n\n- **Provider IDs are immutable.** Once a provider is admitted to the catalog, its ID will never change.\n- **Provider IDs are never reassigned.** If a provider is deprecated (see below), its ID is retired — it will not be reused for a different provider in the future.\n- **New provider IDs may be added at any time.** Integrations should handle unknown provider IDs gracefully (e.g. an unrecognised `providerId` on a voice object should not crash the client).\n\nAPI responses and SDK types that expose a `providerId` string field will always return an ID from this table (or, in the case of a deprecated provider, its historical ID from this table).\n\n## Deprecation Policy\n\nWhen a provider is no longer available through Vokda (e.g. because its upstream service shuts down), the provider ID is **deprecated**, not removed:\n\n1. The provider row is removed from the active catalog listing (`GET /v1/providers`).\n2. The ID remains documented in this file in a **Deprecated Providers** section (see below).\n3. Existing clips, jobs, and historical data that reference the ID continue to resolve normally — the ID stays valid in read paths.\n4. New synthesis requests that target a deprecated provider will receive a `400` with error code `provider_deprecated`.\n5. Deprecated IDs are **never** reassigned.\n\n### Deprecated Providers\n\nNo providers are currently deprecated.\n\n## Changelog Expectation\n\nAny addition, deprecation, or status change of a provider ID will be noted in the project changelog (`CHANGELOG.md` at the repository root) under a **Provider IDs** heading. Consumers that pin to specific providers should monitor those entries.\n", "path": "docs/PROVIDER_IDS.md"}) → wrote docs/PROVIDER_IDS.md (4058 bytes)
